A file is formed of pages. Each have a number of memory words.
A small number of words permits a storage of small arrays (TMS)
A great number of pages permits a storage of many  arrays (TMS)
64  is the default value of page number.
256 is the default value of memory words.

EXAMPLE :
1;      {File Page Number}
256;    {pages}
2;      {Word number of a page of a file}
4096;   {memory words by page}
3;      {Add a file to the MS}
@;      {Return to DEBUT MENU}

After type 99; to save the data and stop.

Begin again the execution of Mefisto.
